This paper deals with the problem of understanding the causal influence of input features on the output of a machine learning classifier. This is a common problem in the field of machine learning, and the paper proposes a novel active learning algorithm to address it. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as this is the most relevant sub-category. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the problem of understanding the causal influence of input features is a fundamental problem in AI. Additionally, the paper deals with image classification, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the problem of bias in machine learning, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
